<HEADLINE> Two Slovak Climbers Die After Scaling Mt. Manaslu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Two of the three Slovak
climbers died after scaling the 8,163-meter high Mt. Manaslu on
October 8 via the northeast route, Nepali Ministry of Tourism and
Civil Aviation said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The two climbers were found dead while returning to their base
camp, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
They came from an 11-member Slovak ski mountaineering
expedition team.  
</P>
</TEXT>
