<HEADLINE> Becker Wins First Group Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- German Boris Becker took a
6-7 (3-7), 6-3, 6-3 vitory over Italian Renzo Furlan Wednesday in
a preliminary group match at the Hong Kong Tennis Championships.
</P>
<P>
Becker will play American Jonathan Stark in his last group
match Friday. A victory would give him a place in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The 12 players in the event are divided into four groups of
three, with the winners of each group advancing to the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Albert Costa, ranked 20th in the world, withdrew from
the tournament due to an injury in his right shoulder. He was
replaced in the Red Group by Australian Peter Tramacchi, who lost
in his first match to compatriot Scott Draper, 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe's Byron Black beat Sweden's Mikael Tillstrom 6-2, 6-7
(3-7), 6-3 in his opening Silver Group match.  
</P>
</TEXT>
