<HEADLINE> Iranian FM Visits Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Iranian Foreign
Minister Kamal Kharazi said in Tajikistan today that his country
supports the Tajikistan's efforts in its internal peace process.
</P>
<P>
Kharazi made the remarks after meeting with Tajik President
Emomali Rakhmonov in Tajikistan's capital Dushanbe, said the
Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Foreign Minister said his country welcomes the
general agreement signed in June between the Tajik government and
its opposition. It aims to establish peace and national
reconciliation within the country.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian government is willing to provide all possible aid
to Tajikistan in its peace process, kharazi said.
</P>
<P>
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami expressed his belief in a
letter to his Tajik counterpart that the goals in the agreement
could be attained.
</P>
<P>
Tajik Prime Minister Yakha Azimov also met with Kharazi
today. They discussed bilateral economic relations and the
establishment of a multilateral commission on economic and trade
cooperation between Tajikistan, Iran, Turkmenistan and
Uzbekistan. 
</P>
