<HEADLINE> McRae Wins In Help of His Teammate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Colin McRae survived his hope of
the world championship after the Scotsman won in the Rally of San
Remo in the help of his teammate Piero Liatti.
</P>
<P>
Liatti led the race for most of the time before the Italian let
his teammate through to win by six seconds after the 25 stages.
</P>
<P>
World championship leader Tommi Makinen of Finland in his
Mitsubishi Lancer and Carlos Sainz of Spain in a Ford Escort
finished third and fourth repectively.
</P>
<P>
Liatti received a 10-second penalty for his deliberate
allowance of McRae's victory. 
</P>
