<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Undertakes Children Rehabilitation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's first lady Grace
Mugabe today officiated at the ground breaking ceremony of the
multi-million dollar Children Rehabilitation Centre, a brain
child of the Children Rehabilitation Trust which she founded.
</P>
<P>
The center will be built with donor funding. Initial costing
of the project would be 42 million Zimbabwe dollars (3.3 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The 17.5-hectare center in Harare will hav a boarding school
and offer vocational training facilities for up to 1,000
children.
</P>
<P>
"Through the proposed Zimbabwe Children's Rehabilitation
Centre, we hope to give expression to the trust's objectives,"
said Mrs. Mugabe, adding "the trust's main objectives are to
ensure welfare of neglected children and that they gain their
self respect."
</P>
<P>
"Once this center is complete, we hope to be able to offer not
only food, clothing and shelter, but also to put the children
through school, afford them some skills training and make sure
they are adequately prepared to fend for themselves in dignified
ways," she added.
</P>
<P>
About 3,000 children live in and sleep on the streets in
Zimbabwe and another 12,000 to 15,000 come daily to the streets
to look for sustenance in a country with about to one million
orphans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
