<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Ghana Conduct Studies for Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia and Ghana are
currently conducting studies on how to create viable conditions
to forge strong social and economic cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, in a
statement to visiting Ethiopian journalists in Accra, Ghana,
Ethiopian ambassador to Ghana Koang Tutlam said the cooperation
between the two countries will focus on areas including
education, health, tourism, trade and investment and civil
aviation.
</P>
<P>
According to the ambassador, Ethiopia currently exports to
Ghana products like spices and horticulture among others and
imports electronics goods and wood products.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said Ethiopia could in the future export to
Ghana live cattle, meat and meat products, hides and leather
products as well as tea while Ghana could supply Ethiopia with
wood products, aluminium goods, cacao, rubber and rubber
products.
</P>
<P>
He added that an export-import ltd. company by the name ASWER
is said to have displayped interest in importing meat to Ghana
and has already begun preparations. 
</P>
