<HEADLINE> Spain Ties Pakistan 1-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Spain played a 1-1 draw to
Pakistan Thursday in a match marred by countroversy over a
disallowed goal at the Champions' Trophy hockey tournament in
Adelaide, Australi.
</P>
<P>
Spain led 1-0 at halftime thanks to a neat goal by forward
Javier Arnau from a penalty corner set piece.
</P>
<P>
After the break, the Pakistanis piled on pressure in search of
an equaliser, but were unable to convert any of four four penalty
corners.
</P>
<P>
Then, from Pakistan's fifth penalty corner in the 62nd minute,
Naveed Alam appeared to flick the ball into the top right corner
of the net.
</P>
<P>
Danish umpire Henrik Ehlers at first allowed the goal but after
consulting Australian umpire Murray Grime, the decision was
reversed.
</P>
<P>
The action was replayed on the large video screen, and one
side-angle shot showed the ball entering the goal and hitting the
top back rail before rebounding out.
</P>
<P>
Minutes later, Pakistan had another goal disallowed for foot
obstruction but in the final minute a converted penalty corner
earned its first point of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Later Thursday, Australia beat the Netherlands 3-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
