<HEADLINE> Czech Republic, Hungary Expand Trade With EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic and
Hungary, both aspiring to joining the European Union (EU), have
expanded their trade with the 15-nation organization.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat, the EU's statistical arm, reported today that the
Czech Republic imports from and exports to the EU accounted for 58
percent of the country's total foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
In Hungary, nearly 60 percent of imports and 63 percent of
exports were conducted with the EU.
</P>
<P>
In the 1993-1996 period, the Czech Republic's imports grew 26
percent annually and exports 15 percent. Hungarian world trade
increased 11.1 percent, twice as much as exports that stood at 5.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
Germany was the largest trading partner with the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic now accounts for 0.6 percent of worldwide
trade and Hungary 0.4 percent. 
</P>
