<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Telecom Upgrades Service Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Telecom has
announced a series of upgrades to its earth station facilities,
the largest in Asia, to further improve its satellite services,
including the introduction of a service level of close to 100
percent availability.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed at satisfying the rapidly growing volume and
rising standards of satellite communications customers.
</P>
<P>
Among the many facility and service enhancements is the
installation of remote-controllable video/audio and Intermediate
Frequency switches at Hong Kong Telecom's earth station and
International TV centers.
</P>
<P>
The company will also install additional dedicated TV equipment
to meet the rising number of international broadcasters to the
region, as well as a new restoration antenna to ensure tighter
monitor and network security.
</P>
<P>
The upgrades are estimated to be close to 50 million HK dollars
(6.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
"As a first step, we are upgrading our facilities to continue
providing services of the highest quality, complemented by a
sophisticated digital infrastructure, advanced equipment and
reliable management and support," said K.W. Chan, manager of
Broadcast and Fixed Satellite Services at Hong Kong Telecom.
</P>
<P>
The next step is to introduce new services and facilities from
the existing Hong Kong Telecom portfolio for customers, Chan
added.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Telecom is Hong Kong's only full-service
telecommunications provider, marketing a comprehensive portfolio
of quality voice and data telecommunication services backed by a
state-of-the-art, fully-digital fiber optic network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
