<HEADLINE> Overseas-Funded Businesses in China Hold Export Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Foreign-funded enterprises
from across China have gathered for an export commodity fair in
south China's Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which opened yesterday in Guangzhou, the capital of
Guangdong, is the ninth one. It will run through the end of the
month.
</P>
<P>
The goods on display include light-industrial products,
textiles, machinery, electronics items, hardware, health care and
farm products, food and edible oils, and building material.
</P>
<P>
More than 1.6 billion US dollars in export contracts were
signed during the previous eight fairs.
</P>
<P>
China has 290,000 overseas-funded projects and has used nearly
200 billion US dollars of overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded businesses now contribute 40 percent of the
country's exports. 
</P>
