<HEADLINE> China Lists 100th B Share in Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 16 (Xinhua) -- China's 100th B share was
listed in the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchange today.
</P>
<P>
China first started trading B shares six years ago, and the
100th B share, Wuling B share, was issued by the Jiangsu Wuling
Group based in Changzhou City, east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
This marks that China has entered a new-round expanding of the
B shares market, through which the country has raised a total of
four billion US dollars in investment from overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Most of the enterprises issuing B shares are state-owned, and
are playing a vital role in China's economy. They have also won
government support to promote their businesses, according to
financial experts.
</P>
<P>
More Chinese enterprises with good economic results will be
allowed to issue B shares in the coming years, as a way to raise
funds for the capital-efficient state sector, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
