<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Caltex Chairman in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu
Bangguo, in a meeting with David J. Law-Smith, chairman and CEO of
the U.S.'s Caltex Petroleum Corp., who is here for the 15th World
Petroleum Congress, said the world's petroleum producers have
expressed a willingness to increase co-operation with Chinese
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Caltex has co-operated with the Chinese for a decade or more,
Wu said, adding that he hopes this can be increased.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that in nearly 20 years, China has made tremendous
progress and that Deng Xiaoping Theory has proven that it can lead
China to prosperity and strength. China will adhere to the reform
and opening-up policy and improve the economic structure and
opening-up for greater economic progress.
</P>
<P>
"We are fully confident of the future and, in the next century,
China will become stronger and even more prosperous," he said.
</P>
<P>
Law-Smith said that China has huge market and a bright future
for development. He said he believes that Caltex's co-operation
with China will be even more successful.
</P>
<P>
Caltex has invested some 200 million U.S. dollars in China,
including a 40-million-dollar wholly-owned lubricant factory,
which is under construction in the bonded area in Tianjin, the
coastal port city near to Beijing. 
</P>
