<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diversion Tunnel at Xiaolangdi Finished </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Three diversion tunnels for
the Xiaolangdi water project on the Yellow River in central
China's Henan province were cleared on Wednesday and are ready for the
damming of the river on October 26.
</P>
<P>
The tunnels will be used to redirect water flow when the river
is dammed.
</P>
<P>
Because October is the dry season, only one tunnel is needed,
said Zhang Ziwei, deputy chief supervisor of the flood relief
project.
</P>
<P>
Work is also under way on a 152-meter-high cofferdam, which will be
283 meters high by the year 2001. So far, 16.6 million cubic
meters of earth and stones, or 32 percent of the amount needed,
have been used at the site.
</P>
<P>
The Xiaolangdi project is 40 km northwest of Luoyang, an
ancient city in central China. It will play an important role in
controlling flooding, reducing silt deposits, and dealing with the
ice menace.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
