<HEADLINE> World Food Day Honored in Northeast Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government today
held a gathering for World Food Day in Dalian, a coastal city in
northeast Liaoning province.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun was among those present at
the gathering.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Minister of Agriculture Bai Zhijian said at the
gathering that the Chinese government has always given top
priority to providing enough food for its people.
</P>
<P>
The country has managed to support its population, which is 22
percent of the world's total, with a mere seven percent of the
world's arable land, he noted.
</P>
<P>
China produced 490 billion kg of grain in 1996, and it is
expected to have another good harvest this year.
</P>
<P>
Ajmal M. Qureshi, Chief Representative of the UN's FAO in
China, spoke highly of the Chinese government's efforts and
policies for developing agriculture.  
</P>
