<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Implement Ruppur Nuclear Power Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
decided to implement the much-awaited Ruppur Nuclear Power Project
which will usher in a new era in the country's energy industry,
the national news agency BSS reported here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The decision was finalized at a meeting of the Ruppur Nuclear
Power Plant Implementation Committee held with Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also reviewed the financing of this ambitious
project and expressed the hope that the donor agencies would
extend necessary help and assistance, BSS said.
</P>
<P>
The epoch-making decision was taken after a long lapse of 34
years, BSS stated.
</P>
<P>
The project will be set up on 290 acres of land in Ruppur under
Pabna district 112 kilometers from Dhaka to meet the growing
demand of electricity in the country, BSS added.
</P>
<P>
The nuclear power plant would generate a huge quantity of power
for the whole country especially for the northern region which is
experiencing serious power shortage, BSS said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
