<HEADLINE> Beijing Expands Co-operation with Taiwan in Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin said
here today that he hopes more Taiwanese will invest in agriculture
in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Jia made the remarks while meeting with 100 Taiwanese experts
who are here for a conference on expanding co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Jia told them that Beijing has a big market, strong scientific
research, and abundant agricultural resources, while Taiwan has
good food processing techniques, and that its experiences could
help Beijing develop more modern agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Many of Beijingers are farmers and they are the major providers
of vegetables and meat for the downtown area.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that 1,500 Taiwan-backed firms are operating in
Beijing, and the municipality has regulations that encourage
investment from Taiwan. "We will further improve the investment
environment for Taiwan compatriots, and better safeguard their
interests," he added. 
</P>
