<HEADLINE> Asian Business Cities to Explore HK Opportunities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 30 delegates from
nine of Asia's top business cities will arrive here next week for
annual meetings of the Business Partner City (BPC) Network, a
senior Hong Kong trade official announced today.
</P>
<P>
"We regard this as an extremely auspicious event, as well as an
important opportunity to strengthen trade links," Raymond Yip,
senior manager for trade promotion of the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council (TDC).
</P>
<P>
The TDC will host the meetings in cooperation with the Osaka
Municipal Government and Business Partner City Council of Osaka,
Japan.
</P>
<P>
All the BPC delegates will have an ideal opportunity to see for
themselves how well the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) of China is functioning after its first 100 days under the
unique "one country, two systems" principle, Yip said.
</P>
<P>
"These meetings will demonstrate the continued confidence of
our Asian neighbors in Hong Kong's future as a regional business
hub and as a priority partner for trade and commerce," he added.
</P>
<P>
The BPC Network is an alliance of trade promotional and
municipal organizations from throughout the Asia-Pacific
region. Also in the network are Singapore, Bangkok, Kuala Lumpur,
Manila, Jakarta, Seoul, Shanghai and Ho Chi Minh City. 
