<P>
TOKYO, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto today praised Hong Kong's economic achievements and
political stability following its return to China on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto made the remark during a 40-minute meeting at his
official residence with Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of China's
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
