<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Position and Guidelines of China's Diplomacy (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fifth, for economic growth, China needs a wide range of
co-operation with the rest of the world on an equal footing. One
of its policies is to open up to the outside world more. Since the
reforms and opening-up started nearly 20 years ago, economic
exchanges with other countries have been growing and playing an
important role in improving its economy and the economy of other
countries.
</P>
<P>
With the intense competition and the rapid development of
science and technology, China should look at the outside world in
an even more positive way, perfect the opening-up, make effective
use of resources both at home and abroad, expand international
markets, and actively participate in regional economic
co-operation and global trade. Diplomacy should continue to serve
all of these.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of China has always placed great importance
on external relations and has paid close attention to one-on-one
diplomacy and the role of trade unions and young people's and
women's organizations in promoting mutual understanding,
friendship, and co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Some people are saying that China's development will pose a
threat to the world, and this has lead to the "China Threat"
theory, but it is totally groundless, because of the following
reasons:
</P>
<P>
A. China for a long time was subjected to acts of aggression,
oppression and humiliation by foreign powers, and it does indeed
know the true meaning of the expression: don't do to others what
you don't want done to yourself.
</P>
<P>
B. It will take several decades to modernize China to the level
of moderately-developed countries because of its large population
and poor economy, so it needs a peaceful international environment.
</P>
<P>
C. China has always had a positive defense-oriented military
strategy, and its military expenditures are very low. The expenses
for 1997 stand at 9.71 billion US dollars, or about 3.6 percent of
the American expenditures. Jiang Zemin said in his report to the
15th Party Congress that China will cut the armed forces by
another 500,000 men over the next three years and will pose no
threat to other countries.
</P>
<P>
D. China has an independent foreign policy of peace, and all
its actions are intended to maintain that peace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971016.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Position and Guidelines of China's Diplomacy (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Sino-US relationship concerns the fundamental interests of
peoples in both countries, as well as peace and development in the
Asian-Pacific Region and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
China and the United States will enter the 21st century with a
comparatively stable relationship so long as the two sides control
the overall situation, look to the future, firmly abide by the
three Sino-US joint communiques and properly handle the Taiwan
issue.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan should draw lessons from history, observe the
Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and the Sino-Japanese Treaty of
Peace and Friendship, follow the correct road for the development
of bilateral relations, engage in joint efforts to ensure the
fundamental interests of the peoples in the two countries, and
promote peace and development in the Asian-Pacific Region.
</P>
<P>
We should practice mutual respect while seeking common ground,
equality and mutual benefits and reserving differences and should
work with Western European countries to build a new cooperative
relationship geared to the 21st century. We should also continue
to improve and develop friendly relations with Canada, Australia
and other developed countries.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin's report at the 15th National Congress of
 Communist Party of China emphasized: "We should adhere to the
good-neighborly policy. Our consistent stand will never change."
President Jiang's statement was a solemn declaration of policy.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, China has worked hard to develop mutually
beneficial friendly cooperation with neighboring
countries. Efforts have also centered on maintaining a sound and
peaceful environment.
</P>
<P>
Historical factors and various other reasons have sparked some
differences or disputes between China and surrounding
countries. This is quite understandable and the key point centers
on how to properly treat related issues. We should peacefully
resolve the issues through friendly consultations and negotiations
in an effort to maintain the overall peaceful and stable
situation. We should put aside differences for the time being and
seek common ground while reserving differences.
</P>
<P>
China is currently concentrating on economic construction and
it is therefore important to maintain a peaceful and stable
surrounding environment in order to guarantee a smooth development
of the modernization drive. This will in turn promote better
relations between China and surrounding countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
