<HEADLINE> Adherence to Theory of Primary Stage of Socialism  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- The people are concentrating on building material wealth and
promoting ethical and moral progress in line with the common goal
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics and;
</P>
<P>
-- The gap between China and the advanced world levels will
gradually narrow and China will accomplish national revitalization
on the basis of socialism.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that "accomplishing the historical process will
require at least 100 years". He quoted Deng Xiaoping's words that
"consolidating and developing the socialist system will require a
long historical period, and the persistent efforts of several, or
even dozens of generation."
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the conditions of socialism will require
China to undergo a long primary stage in order to realize
industrialization and perfect a modern market economy.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot skip this historical period," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's report to the 15th Party congress reiterated that the
fundamental task for the primary stage is to develop social
productity. Therefore, the Party and country must focus on
economic construction, with all other work subject to and serving
the central task.
</P>
<P>
One sociologist said that productivity is the deciding force
for any social development. He noted that the development of
productivity is vital for consolidating and developing socialism,
as well as for lifting socialism from a lower to a higher stage
and ensuring the ultimate realization of Communism.
</P>
<P>
He reasoned that anything conducive to developing social
productivity should conform to the fundamental interests of the
people, and should therefore fulfil all requirements and be
accepted by socialism, and vice versa.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that it has a direct bearing on and is decisively
important with regard to developing socialist productivity as
the starting pointing for all work under the present historical
conditions".
</P>
<P>
The theory of the primary stage of socialism has been accepted
as the Party's guideline for leading the people to advance the
cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics from now
through the middle of the next century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
