<HEADLINE> Air Macao Expects First Net Profit This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leonel Miranda, president of the Executive Committee of Air
Macao, told the Portuguese News Agency Lusa today that the
company's business is unexpectedly "very good."
</P>
<P>
Having started commercial operation in November 1995, Air Macao
reported a loss of 37 million patacas (about 4.68 million
U.S. dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
The company had expected a loss of 22 million patacas (about
2.78 million U.S. dollars) for this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
The unexpected good business is a result of surging number of
passengers this year, plus a stricter control of the company's
expenditure, he said.
</P>
<P>
The company has carried a total of 1.3 million passengers
since its commercial operation.
</P>
<P>
Air Macao plans to launch a new daily service to Fuzhou,
capital of coastal Fujian Province on October 26. By then, its
weekly fights will increase to 105 and its fleet will fly between
Macao and ten other destinations.  
