<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined sharply
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index plunged by 50.79 points to close at 1804.24 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 141.4 million units, worth
401.03 million Singapore dollars (about 258.73 million U.S.
dollars). Declines continued to overwhelm advances by 243 to 87,
while 285 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NatSteel Elec was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 8.97 million units. It was followed by
Transit which had 5.34 million shares traded. NatSteel was next
with 4.76 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 1.1 dollars to close at 38.7 Singapore
dollars. The United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign increased by 50
cents to end at 11.3 Singapore dollars. Uniphoenix picked up by 20
cents to finish at 7.8 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, ASEAN Fund was the biggest loser as it fell by
80 cents to end at 11.2 U.S. dollars. Local car distributor Cycle
&AMP; Carriage and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign declined
by 60 cents each to finish at 7.6 and 22.3 Singapore dollars
respectively. Keppel FELS lost 55 cents to close at 4.6 Singapore
dollars.  
</P>
