<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- China Scholars Abroad (CSA),
China's first monthly magazine whose readers are mainly overseas
Chinese students, celebrated its 10th anniversary today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Chen Siyuan, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, attended the anniversary celebration
along with Zhu Kaixuan, minister in charge of the State Education
Commission, and about 100 scholars and students who have returned
from foreign countries.
</P>
