CSA published China's first weekly, Electronic Journal, in 1995
to give overseas scholars the latest information about China
through the Internet, where it is called "Voice from Beijing " by
its readers.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping, chief architect of China's reform, who also
studied abroad in the 1920s, wrote the name for the monthly,
according to sources. 
