<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S Sanctions Hurt Business Relations: Chevron Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua)-- Amid positive global business
trends, the U.S sanctions against various countries seldom resolve
political concerns, but often hurt the business relationships that
form the bridge for positive interaction on those concerns, a
Chevron official said here today.
</P>
<P>
In a keynote speech at the 15th World Petroleum Congress (WPC),
Kenneth T. Derr, chairman of the board and chief executive officer
of Chevron Corporation, said he hoped more leaders will see that
active business relationships contribute far more to human
progress than sanctions ever could.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks in his speech titled "Competitive
Imperatives and Critical Challenges for the Global Oil Industry",
which values partnership and cooperation in the sound development
of oil industry as well as the whole global economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
