<HEADLINE> Sino-Saudi Arabian Friendship Association Formed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a
reception here today to mark the establishment of the Sino-Saudi
Arabian Friendship Association and the Saudi Arabian-Chinese
Friendship Association.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reception, CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan said the
establishment of the two associations puts up two bridges linking
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Since the forging of Sino-Saudi Arabian diplomatic ties in
1990, friendly cooperation has grown, said Qi, who is the
president of the Sino-Saudi Arabian Friendship Association.
</P>
<P>
Qi said he hoped the two associations, as fixed channels for
non-governmental exchanges, could play a role in deepening mutual
understanding, bilateral friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Rahman Al-Jeraisy, president of the Saudi Arabian-Chinese
Friendship Association, said Saudi Arabia attaches great
significance to its friendly relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Yousef M. Al-Madani, Saudi Arabian Ambassador to China, said
the establishment of the two associations will play a long-term
and positive role in expanding cooperation between the two peoples
in political, trade and economic areas. 
</P>
