<DOCNO> XIE19971016.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 15th World Petroleum Congress Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The 15th World Petroleum
Congress (WPC) closed here this afternoon after five days of
intensive discussions on prospects of the world energy industry.
</P>
<P>
More than 5,000 officials, senior managers and researchers
exchanged views on major issues concerning future trends of the
petroleum industry during the congress.
</P>
<P>
The participants reached consensus that technological
advancement and global cooperation will be the key factor to
further development of the industry in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, major efforts should be made by both sides on demand
and supply worldwide to ensure a relative stability of the
international petroleum market, participants urged.
</P>
<P>
The next World Petroleum Congress will be held in Calgary of
Canada in the year 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
