in Jerusalem for illegally selling explosives to Palestinians,
including Islamic militants, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
The arrested are authorized workers to carry out detonation
works in quarries inside Israel, but they also worked in quarries
within the Palestinian territories. (Israel-Crackdown-Arrests)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif said here
today that the eight percent devaluation of rupee against the
U.S. dollar would boost exports and improve the overall economic
situation in the country.
</P>
<P>
The State Bank of Pakistan on Wednesday adjusted the
dollar-rupee (buying) rate by 8.71 percent from 40.52 rupees to a
U.S. dollar to 44.05 rupees. (Pakistan-Sharif-Rupee Readjustment)
</P>
