</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Indian Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral called
Wednesday for a universal extradition treaty and suggested that an
internationally acceptable code of conduct for governments should
be evolved to check various crimes around the world, local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Gujral said that though a universal extradition treaty could
form part of the United Nations agenda, some international
conventions will have to be built to save the countries from the
agonizing negotiations in seeking the extradition of wanted
criminals. (India-PM-Extradition Treaty)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The death toll from drought in eastern Indonesia has
climbed to 445 people, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Of the victims, 398 were in Jayawijaya District, 23 in the
neighboring district of Merauke to the south and 24 in Puncakjaya
District to the west, Kompas said.
</P>
<P>
Some local experts predicted that the long-awaited monsoon rain
would come in November, but some ecologists forecast that the rain
would come in January. (Indonesia-Death-Drought)  
</P>
