<HEADLINE> Ample Worldwide Oil Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Human beings will be able to
enjoy oil resources for several more centuries, according to noted
experts attending the 15th World Petroleum Congress.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that mankind has consumed roughly 500 billion
barrels (80 billion tons of oil), or 85 percent of proven deposits
at in the early in 1973.
</P>
<P>
The discovery of new oilfields has almost doubled the figure
for proven reserves. Experts note that known oil reserves will
last for 44 years in line with the current production capacity.
</P>
<P>
However, reports indicate a continuous rise in global oil
deposits.
</P>
<P>
Expers note the difficulty in accurately projecting the figure
because of large-scale investments required for geological
prospecting, and the fact that earning profits requires many years
of exploration efforts.
</P>
<P>
Scientists recently completed an extensive investigation which
found massive liquefied methane deposits in the earth's permafrost
belt and in the oceans. The scientists estimated said reserves
will last for several hundred years.
</P>
<P>
Major countries are currently planning to drill wells to depths
of ten km in preparation for large-scale development in the next
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
