<HEADLINE> Zambia Not to Privatize Public Media </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has said
it will not privatize public media as demanded by a back-bencher,
"Times of Zambia" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Tourism Minister Amusaa Mwanamwambwa told parliament here on
Wednesday that Times of Zambia, Zambia Daily Mail, Zambia
National Broadcasting Corporation (ZNBC), Zambia News Agency
(ZANA) and Zambia Information Service (ZIS) are not for sale.
</P>
