<HEADLINE> Private Sector in East China Province Develops Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Private enterprises in east
China's Anhui province have developed rapidly, with an
average annual growth rate of 60 percent in the last five years.
</P>
<P>
The figure was 17 percentage points more than the national
average for the corresponding period.
</P>
<P>
The province's 17,600 private enterprises have over 250,000
employees and total registered capital of six billion yuan (730
million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Some 900 private enterprises have over one million yuan in
registered capital each and some 100 others exceed 10 million yuan
each.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 46 percent of the private enterprises
are engaged in manufacturing industries, with 42 percent in the
service sector.
</P>
<P>
Experts expect the proportion of the province's service sector
to rise along with the rapid development of private enterprises.
</P>
