<DOCNO> XIE19971016.0234 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Develops High-tech Fire Control Device </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 16 (Xinhua) -- An automatic device for
locating and extinguishing fires has been developed in Northeast
China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The device, produced by the Liaoning Branch of the China Fire
Control Society, can locate a fire after three seconds of scanning
and spray the blaze until it is extinguished.
</P>
<P>
Compared with present automatic fire-control systems in use
worldwide, the device is not only water-saving but also can spray
all around, experts say.
</P>
<P>
A logic control system allows the device to distinguish fire
from sunlight, lamps, photography flashes and lighters. It can be
easily linked to fire hydrant networks and other water networks.
</P>
<P>
In addition, it costs only one third of current fire-control
devices.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
