<HEADLINE> Defense Show Opens in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh International
Defense Equipment Exhibition and Conference opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The world's leading arms companies from the United States,
Australia, Sweden, Finland, France, Canada, Germany, Britain,
Thailand and some other countries unveiled their military
equipment at the three-day defense show, which is supported by the
Thai Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Armed Forces have also put on show made-in-Thailand
defense products, such as the 105mm field gun, combat helmets, a
rocket launcher, flak jackets and laser range finders.
</P>
<P>
Military equipment producers are represented at the show to win
the confidence of the visiting military personnel, which is the
first step toward winning military procurement contracts, said
Chaw Kongpoolsilpa, chairman of Conferences, Exhibitions and
Management Services, the organizer of the arms show known as
Defense Asia '97.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 dignitaries, senior military strategists, arms
suppliers and potential arms purchasers have been invited to view
some of the latest defense equipment and find potential arms
supplies for their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The event also includes a conference on defense technology,
whose topics include arms and defense procurement in the 21st
century and new standard for tactical communication, and
presentations on submarine design, logistics support and other
issues.
</P>
<P>
Defense Asia '97 will be followed by another defense
exhibition, Thai 97, at U-Tapao and Sattahip military bases on the
eastern seaboard of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Combat aircraft and live firing demonstrations are planned as
part of the show of military aircraft and warships.  
</P>
