<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Forms Body for Talks With Foreign Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladesh government has
formed an eight-member committee to begin negotiations with 21
foreign oil companies on oil and gas exploration in the country's
12 blocks, Energy Ministry sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The negotiations will begin on October 21 and conclude on
December 10, the sources said, adding that production sharing
contracts (PSCs) are expected to be signed with qualified
companies by December 15.
</P>
