the government and the companies "on a per block per company
basis," the sources stated.
</P>
<P>
The Energy Ministry has already given the timetable to the 21
companies which have submitted proposals in the second bidding for
exploration blocks in Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The companies submitted 28 proposals on July 15 this year for
the 12 blocks, nine on-shore and three off-shore.
</P>
<P>
They include those from Australia, France, Canada, the United
States, Denmark, Britain and Malaysia, the sources added.
