<HEADLINE> China to Issue Global Bonds Worth 500 Million U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Finance
announced here today that China will issue global bonds worth 500
million U.S. dollars shortly.
</P>
<P>
This will be the third time the ministry has issued U.S.
dollar-denominated global bonds since 1994.
</P>
<P>
Merrill Lynch International Inc. and J.P. Morgan will be joint
underwriters of the issue, offering the bonds simultaneously in
the United States, Asia and Europe. The bonds will also be listed
in Hong Kong and Luxemburg.
</P>
<P>
Chinese officials said the ministry planned the bond issue as a
move to improve links with leading investors in the United States,
Asia and Europe and to establish the issuance of long-term bonds
overseas, so as to raise more funds for China's major construction
projects. 
</P>
