<HEADLINE> Israel Seeks Economic Cooperation With Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 16 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of Israeli
industrialists is currently in Myanmar seeking ways to promote
economic cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli delegation, led by Amir Makov, chairman of the
Board of Export Institute, called on Secretary of the Myanmar
Investment Commission and Minister at the Office of the Deputy
Prime Minister Maung Maung here Wednesday, the official paper The
New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation also met with officials of the Myanmar Ministry
of National Planning and Economic Development and Ministry of
Industry to explore ways to extend economic and industrial
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In the last few days, some 56 Myanmar graduates, the fourth
batch, were sent to Israel to attend a practical one-year on-job
farming course conducted by the host country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Koor Industries of Israel signed a memorandum of
understanding with the Myanmar Ministry of National Planning and
Economic Development in February last year on economic
cooperation, according to an earlier official report.
</P>
<P>
Israel is among the 22 countries or regions with an investment
of 2.4 million U.S. dollars in a single project in Myanmar at the
end of September this year, according to official statistics.
</P>
