<HEADLINE> Guangxi Successful in Dealing with Drug Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhang Autonomous
Region, south China, stepped up crackdown on drug-related crimes
and settled altogether 7,447 cases in the first nine months of
this year, representing a 54.4 percent increase over 1996 same
period.
</P>
<P>
Local police seized from January to September a total of 149
kilograms drugs and arrested some 9,000 people involved in drug
trafficking or drug abuse. and 235 of them have been sentenced to
varying prison terms.
</P>
<P>
With long coastal and border lines, Guangxi has witnessed an
rise in drug-related crimes over recent years. The autonomous
regional authorities therefore have taken a series of coercive
measures to stem the spreading of drugs, including launching a
large-scale educational campaign to help raise the people's
awareness against drugs.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the autonomous region has established 89 drug
rehabilitation centers where hundreds of experts, doctors and
instructors and, as a result, over 10,000 addicts have abandoned
drug addiction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
