<HEADLINE> Ecuadoran Mission to Promote Trade With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- An Ecuadoran governmental mission
will visit China from October 21 to 23 to negotiate over an accord
which aims to attract Chinese investment to Ecuador and to
increase bilateral trade, the Foreign Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
Vice Foreign Minister, Gonzalo Salvador, said Ecuador is
looking forward to promoting trade with China, since China has
transformed "from an emerging market to a principal one".
</P>
<P>
"China is an outstanding country for the future of Ecuadoran
trade", he said, noting that Ecuador`s banana exports to China
boosted to 360,000 tons in 1996 from 40,000 tons in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The vice minister explained Ecuador also expects to expand its
sales of fresh flowers, shrimp and seafood to China.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade between Ecuador and China averages at 67
million U.S. dollars a year.
</P>
<P>
Salvador said that Ecuador will also look for Chinese companies
willing to invest in sectors such as mines, oil, electric power
and capital assets.
</P>
<P>
Chinese enterprises are also considering establishing farm
tractor assembly plants in Ecuador, he said. 
</P>
