<HEADLINE> Thailand to Speed Up Privatization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government is to speed
up the privatization of 66 state enterprises so that the process
can be completed within five years.
</P>
<P>
The five-year plan will be considered today by a committee
supervising policy for state enterprises, chaired by Deputy Prime
Minister Thaksin Shinawatra, press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Thaksin was quoted as saying the main purpose of privatization
would be to increase the efficiency of the enterprises since they
play a significant role in economic development.
</P>
<P>
