<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poland's Ruling Alliance Nominates PM Candidate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The ruling Polish alliance
recommended Kerzy Buzek to President Aleksander Kwasniewski as the
prime minister candidate here today.
</P>
<P>
The alliance is composed of the United Election Campaign
Alliance (UECA) and the Free Alliance (the Unia Walnosci).
</P>
<P>
The UECA led by the Solidarity Trade Union got 33.83 percent of
the votes in the parliamentary election held on September 21 and
won the right to form the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The UECA and the Free Alliance, after intense negotiations,
reached an agreement yesterday on the formation of a ruling
alliance and the selection of a common prime minister candidate.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski met with leaders of the UECA and Kerzy Buzek at the
presidential palace this afternoon, the Polska Agencja Prasowa
reported.
</P>
<P>
After one and a half hour's talks, the president's spokesman
told the press that Kwasniewski would appoint Buzek as the
chairman of the Council of Ministers.
</P>
<P>
Buzek, 57, was graduated from the Silesian Institute of
Technology and is now a researcher at the Institute of Chemical
Engineering under the Polish Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
He was elected member of the parliament in a recent election.
</P>
