<HEADLINE> OPEC Urges More Technology Transfer in Global Oil Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- OPEC should have access to the
best facilities in order to maximize the value of their natural
resources, though its member countries are blessed highly
competitive costs for both exploration and development, said
Rilwanu Lukman, secretary general of OPEC, at the plenary meeting
of 15th World Petroleum Congress today.
</P>
<P>
The global oil industry has undergone considerable development
since 1970s, he said. however, "the transfer of technology to
developing countries is still very much an issue of concern," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC member countries have thus far implemented legislation
that encourages sustainable and economic exploration of their
existing oil reserves as well as the search for new reserves,
according to the secretary general.
</P>
<P>
He said it is now generally recognized that the transfer of
technology in the oil industry is most likely to take the form of
joint ventures or other types of partnership between OPEC members
and the western oil companies.
</P>
<P>
Some of the OPEC members have increased the level of foreign
participation in their oil industries in order to improve their
access to the advanced upstream and downstream petroleum
technology, said Lukman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
