to Brazil Wednesday without making significant progress in the
process of setting up the Free Trade Area of the Americas (FTAA)
even though he managed to reach several accords.
</P>
<P>
Clinton left here for Buenos Aires, capital of Argentina, the
last leg of a week-long trip that also took him to Venezuela and
Brazil. He will return to Washington on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
During Clinton's two-day visit to Brazil, the two countries
signed seven cooperation agreements on education, space,
environment, peaceful use of nuclear energy, the fight against
drug trafficking and the extradition process.
(Clinton-Brazil-Visit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
