<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Top Leader Meets Iraqi Deputy PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's top leader Do Muoi and
visiting Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Mohammed Hamza al-Zubaidi
Wednesday vowed to further strengthen bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Do Muoi, General Secretary of the Communist Party of Vietnam,
told al-Zubaidi that he was pleased with "the fine development of
friendship and comprehensive cooperation between the two
countries", according to the Vietnam News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese leader stressed that Vietnam has always attached
importance to the preservation and development of "solidarity, and
multi-faceted and long-term cooperation" with Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"Under the leadership of president Saddam Hussein," Do Muoi
believed, "the Iraqi people would overcome current difficulties
and trials to build a prosperous country."
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, al-Zubaidi affirmed that Iraq valued the
cooperation with Vietnam, especially in the fields of commerce,
agriculture, oil and gas industry and personnel training.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi deputy prime minister, who highly appreciated
Vietnam's solidarity and active assistance to Iraq, believed that
such close cooperation between the two countries would be further
consolidated and expanded. 
</P>
