<HEADLINE> Hungary's Real Wage Increase Surpasses Rate of Inflation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The increase in real wages for
Hungarian citizens this year surpassed the increase in prices,
the nation's Central Bureau of Statistics said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the recent figures released by the bureau, the
average monthly wage for a person during the first eight months of
this year was 36,250 Forint (about 196 U.S. dollars), a 24.8
percent increase over the same period last year, a figure higher
than the 18.5 percent increase in prices for the same time.
</P>
<P>
This indicates the Hungarian economy has improved markedly in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, the rate of increase in real wages has always been
lower than the inflation rate, with the exception of 1994.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
