<HEADLINE> Sharp Growth In Foreign Trade In North China Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The foreign trade of Tianjin in
north China had a 22 percent increase in the first nine months of
the year, amounting to 6.2 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports in the past nine months increased by 20.2 percent to
3.49 billion dollars, and imports by 20.2 percent, to 2.7 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Trade of the city's foreign-funded enterprises amounted to 4.57
billion dollars, up 33 percent from the same period of last year,
according to local trade officials.
</P>
<P>
The figure accounts for nearly 70 percent of the city's total,
they said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade enterprises did more than 1.3 billion dollars in
business, an increase of 38 percent on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
Export licenses have been issued to 288 enterprises, 230 of
them this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
