<HEADLINE> Brazil, U.S. to Take Joint Action Against Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Brazil and the United
States will perform a joint operation to fight against drug
trafficking in the Amazon zone in January.
</P>
<P>
The operation will evaluate Brazil's capacity to pursue drug
traffickers and illicit crop growers, local press reports quoted
Gen. Barry McCaffrey, chief of the U.S. Office of National Drug
Control Policy, as saying today.
</P>
