visit to Brazil that ended today, said the joint maneuver was
accorded with Chief of General Staff of the Brazilian Armed
Forces, Gen. Benedito Leonel, and Defense Minister Iris Resende.
</P>
<P>
"It is very important for the U.S. government to know about
Brazil's efforts to cope with the drug problem. We are looking
for cooperation in that issue on the basis of unharming our
sovereignty," Resende said. 
