<HEADLINE> Green Awarded in Lawsuit Against Tyson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 15 (Xinhua) -- American boxer Mitch Green on
Wednesday was awarded 45,000 U.S. dollars by a New York jury in a
civil lawsuit against former world champion Mike Tyson.
</P>
<P>
Green filed the suit seeking 25 million dollars for alleged
assault and battery, but the jury was unanimous in agreeing that
he was not entitled to any punitive damages.
</P>
<P>
The award by the six-person jury in New York State Supreme
Court was for pain and suffering that Green sustained from Tyson
outside a leather clothing store here on August 23, 1988.
</P>
<P>
The jury ruled unanimously that Green had provoked Tyson and
reduced the initial 100,000 dollars it agreed upon by 55 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
