<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Cracks Down on Fake Foreign Trade Marks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 16 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province is cracking down on the misappropriation of foreign
trademarks.
</P>
<P>
Ninety percent of foreign trademark infringement cases
uncovered by authorities have taken place in the Pearl River Delta
and other coastal areas in Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
Famous trademarks such as "Sony", "Toshiba" and "Apple" have
become targets in infringement cases, while products labeled with
fake trademarks are mainly clothes, food and electric home
appliances.
</P>
<P>
Since 1983, when the country issued the Law on Trademark,
Guangdong has handled more than 3,200 infringement cases, and
confiscated 50,000 pieces of false trademarks. 
</P>
