<HEADLINE> McRae Wins Italian Auto Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Scotman Colin McRae finished a
comeback on Wednesday when he won the Auto Rally of Italy and made
his bid possible for the world title.
</P>
<P>
McRae, world champion in 1995, finished ahead even though his
Subaru teammate Pierro Liatti of Italy came home first.
</P>
<P>
Liatti was given a 10-second penalty for arriving late at the
final service check.
</P>
