<HEADLINE> IDB Okays 60 Mln Dlrs for Low-Income Housing in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 60
million U.S. dollar loan to Guatemala to help improve its housing
market and investment in housing for low-income households.
</P>
<P>
The program will introduce demand-side subsidies that will
allow some households to improve their existing housing. Other
households will use the subsidies, together with their own
savings, to gain access to commercial mortgages.
</P>
<P>
The private sector will be entirely responsible for producing
the houses and supplying the credit.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 40,000 households will benefit from housing
subsidies of up to 2,000 dollars, while 50,000 households in the
informal sector will receive legal titles to their properties
through the regulatory reform.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is estimated at 108.8 million
dollars. Local counterpart funds total 48.8 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
